Forest fires in north-east China hadflared again, threatening settlements and virgin forests so faruntouched by the blaze, the official press said.    The New China News Agency said eight new fires had beendiscovered in the Inner Mongolia region and were rapidlyspreading north and west. It said rain forecast for the regionwas expected to help contain them.    The China Daily said fires near the town of Tahe to theeast had re-kindled and were moving towards nearby loggingcamps. Soldiers have been called in to fight the blaze.    The fires which began on May 6 have killed 191 people. REUTER&#3;